
<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml">

  <Paragraph>
This sample illustrates how to navigate between bookmarks in a Word document using Essential DocIO. Bookmark navigation let the user to switch the control or cursor to a specific bookmark and let the user to modify, edit or delete the contents on it.
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph>
Below is the illustration of the output document.
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph TextAlignment ="Center">
<Image Source="Images\sample.png" Height="530" Stretch="None"/>
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Style="{DynamicResource HeaderParagraphStyle}">Features:</Paragraph> 
<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph>	Supports navigation using bookmarks in a Word document.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>	Supports appending or removing contents to an existing bookmark.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>	Supports Bookmark content replacement among tables, sections and paragraphs.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>
</FlowDocument>
